50|$|Rt Hon Arthur Creech Jones was Secretary of State for the Colonies from October 1946 until February 1950, {{appropriately}} {{given that}} in June 1936 {{he pressed the}} Government, who were encouraging Colonies to set up memorials to King George V, to {{follow the example of}} Uganda and set up a technical educational institution. The Labour Party nominated him to the Colonial Office's Educational Advisory Committee in 1936, on which he served for nine years. In 1937, he was {{a founding member of the}} <b>Trades</b> <b>Union</b> Congress Colonial <b>Affairs</b> Committee, and in 1940 he founded the Fabian Colonial Bureau.|$|R
